---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import FormattedDate from '../components/FormattedDate.astro';

const title = "About Me";
const description = "A developer who commits like it's a heartbeat.";
const pubDate = new Date(); // Using current date for "About Me"
const heroImage = "/blog-placeholder-about.jpg"; // You might want to change this
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={title} description={description} />
		<style>
			main {
				width: 720px;
				max-width: calc(100% - 2em);
				margin: auto;
				padding: 1em;
			}
			.hero-image {
				width: 100%;
				margin-bottom: 1em;
			}
			.hero-image img {
				display: block;
				margin: 0 auto;
				border-radius: 12px;
				box-shadow: var(--box-shadow);
			}
			.prose {
				width: 720px;
				max-width: calc(100% - 2em);
				margin: auto;
				padding: 1em;
				color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
			}
			.title-section {
				margin-bottom: 1em;
				padding: 1em 0;
				text-align: center;
				line-height: 1;
			}
			.title-section h1 {
				margin: 0 0 0.5em 0;
			}
			.date {
				margin-bottom: 0.5em;
				color: rgb(var(--gray));
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<article>
				{heroImage && (
					<div class="hero-image">
						<img width={1020} height={510} src={heroImage} alt="About me hero image" />
					</div>
				)}
				<div class="prose">
					<div class="title-section">
						<h1>{title}</h1>
						<div class="date">
							<FormattedDate date={pubDate} />
						</div>
						<hr />
					</div>
					<p>
						Hello there! I'm a software developer who lives and breathes code. For me, committing isn't just a task; it's a rhythm, a constant pulse that drives my projects forward. You could say I commit like it's a heartbeat â€“ steady, frequent, and essential to keeping everything alive and thriving.
					</p>
					<p>
						I thrive on the iterative process of building, refining, and shipping. Each commit represents a small step, a piece of a larger puzzle, and a testament to the continuous effort I pour into my work. Whether it's a new feature, a bug fix, or a tiny refactor, every contribution matters.
					</p>
					<p>
						This dedication to consistent progress isn't just about a clean Git history (though that's a nice bonus!). It's about a mindset: always improving, always learning, and always pushing the boundaries of what's possible with technology. I believe that great software is built one heartbeat, one commit, at a time.
					</p>
					<p>
						When I'm not crafting code, you might find me exploring new technologies, contributing to open-source projects, or simply enjoying the challenge of a complex problem. If you're looking for a developer who is passionate, dedicated, and brings a relentless energy to their work, you've come to the right place.
					</p>
				</div>
			</article>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
